  <div id="story" class="text">
    
    <h2> Story </h2>
    <p>
      Pierre tends to check Berkeley <a href="http://events.berkeley.edu/index.php">events</a>                                                                                     pretty often, especially the Neuroscience and EECS calendars. He was getting tired of navigating to                                                                               a bunch of pages to see what was happening tomorrow. 
    </p>

    <p>
      He mentioned the clumsy events navigation to Luba. He said he had the same issue, 
      so together they decided to build a better website for Berkeley events.
    </p>

    <p>
      Soon after, Derrick saw the potential and usefulness of the site, and joined the team.
    </p>

    <p>
      The trio hopes to create a single one-stop website for all Berkeley events.
    </p>

    <p>
      Future features:
      <ul>
        <li> Include student organization events from Facebook </li>
        <li> Daily (opt-in) email feeds of interesting events </li>
        <li> Share links of events </li>
      </ul>
    </p>
